Setter And Getter Method
============
===============
====================
we can set and get the values of instance variable by using setter and getter methods
=================
=======================
=============================

Setter Method
============
==============
=================

Setter methods can be used to set values of instance variables , setter methods are also known as 
Mutator methods

{ A mutator method is a method used to control changes to a variable. They are also widely known as setter methods.
  Often a setter is accompanied by a getter (together also known as accessors), which returns the value of the private member variable.}

=========================
=========================================Syntax====================================
===================================================================================

def   setVariable(self,variable):
	self.variable=variable

Ex--
=====
=======
def  setName(self,name):
	self.name=name


===================================================================================
===================================================================================

2--Getter Methods
================
===================

Getter method use to get the values of instance variables , getter method also known as 
accessor methods

===================================================================================
=========================================Syntax====================================

def  getVariable(self):
	return self.variable

Ex--
====
=====

def  getName(self):
	return self.name
 
===================================================================================
===================================================================================
=================================Program of Setter and Getter=========================
===================================================================================

class Student:
    def setName(self,name):
        self.name=name
        
    def getName(self):
        return self.name
    def setMarks(self,marks):
        self.marks=marks
    def getMarks(self):
        return self.marks
    
n=int(input("Enter the Number of Student:: "))
for i in range(n):
    s=Student()
    name=input("Enter Student Name:: ")
    s.setName(name)
    marks=int(input("Enter the Marks:: "))
    s.setMarks(marks)
print("Hiii ",s.getName())
print("Your Marks are: ",s.getMarks())

